Ecological notes : very common in all types of woodland and carr; heathland; moorland; wetlands including fens, mires, bogs and water meadows; grassland; scrub; old hedges; old sand and gravel workings; marginal vegetation by upland lake; calcareous valley; parkland; gardens; saltmarsh and reed beds; coastal sand dunes; open montane habitats.
